  "nursesNote": "A therapeutic milieu is a planned, structured environment in which the unit itself, the daily routine, and group activities all support healing, not just medications and individual therapy. Safety, both physical and emotional, is the top priority. The nurse provides a predictable routine with clear, consistent limits applied the same way by all staff, offers groups and activities to practice coping and social skills, and treats every interaction as therapeutic by role-modeling calm, respectful behavior. Patients share in decisions (community meetings) and are treated with dignity and respect. Consistency across the team builds trust and a sense of safety.",
  "providerOrders": [
    "Maintain physical and emotional safety on the unit",
    "Provide a predictable routine with consistent limits",
    "Offer groups and activities to build coping and social skills",
    "Treat every interaction as therapeutic and role-model behavior",
    "Involve patients in their care and decisions"
  ],
